<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-01T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="596" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">647.116/139: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Melbourne</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dye</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Melbourne</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-01T18:00:00+10:00">June
                                        1, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received June 1—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>From Moffat. I presented note to Sir George Pearce this morning.
                                Although he recognized the drawbacks and risks inherent in a
                                deliberate attempt to divert trade, he held out no hope of any
                                modification of the Government’s policy or of nondiscrimination in
                                its application. Details of conversation by despatch.<note n="13" xml:id="d596fn13">Despatch No. 215, June 3; not printed.</note>
                                Returning to Sydney, due Wednesday evening. [Moffat.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dye</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>